Cell.Text: So, what do we have here? Hmm. Let me guess. | By your scent, I'd say you were from the Guild. But that can't be true, because I told Mercer I wouldn't deal with them anymore.

Node.Caption: TG04GulumEiInitialBranchTopic

Cell.Text: I don't deal in land or property. Now, if you're looking for goods, you've come to the right person.
Oh, wait... did you say Goldenglow Estate? My apologies. | I'm sorry to say I know very little about that... bee farm, was it?

Node.Caption: TG04GulumEiInitialBranchTopic02: You can drop the act now... Gajul-Lei.

Cell.Text: Maybe I did, maybe I didn't. I can't be expected to remember every deal I handle.

Node.Caption: TG04GulumEiInitialBranchTopic04: You acted as a broker for its new owner.

Cell.Text: [S] Well, now that you mention it, there is something I've been trying to get my hands on.

Node.Caption: TG04GulumEiInitialBranchTopic05: What would it take to identify the buyer? (Bribe)

Node.ToolTip:

Cell.Text: [S] All right. Had I known the deal would bring me this much trouble, I never would have accepted the gold.
I don't care what you promise. If I tell you the buyer's name and word gets around, it could ruin me!

Node.Caption: TG04GulumEiInitialBranchTopic04a: Identify the buyer and we'll forget what we know. (Persuade)

Cell.Text: Not at all. I tend not to ask too many questions when I'm on the job. I'm sure you understand. | However, I did notice she was quite angry and it was being directed at Mercer Frey.

Node.Caption: TG04GulumEiFirebrandWineBranchTopic02: Did she say why she was doing this?

Cell.Text: I was approached by a woman who wanted me to act as the broker for something big. | She flashed a bag of gold in my face and said all I had to do was pay Aringoth for the estate. | I brought him the coin and walked away with her copy of the deed.

Node.Caption: TG04GulumEiFirebrandWineBranchTopic01: What about the information on Goldenglow Estate?

Cell.Text: In this business we rarely deal in names; our identity comes from how much coin we carry.

Node.Caption: TG04GulumEiFirebrandWineBranchTopic03: That's it? No name or anything?

Node.ToolTip:

Last User:ananes Date:4/11/2011 File:Skyrim.esm

Cell.Text: [S] G|Look, that's all I know. I never promised you I'd have all the answers. | Now, since our transaction is done, I'll be on my way.

Node.Caption: TG04GulumEiFirebrandWineBranchTopic04: I think you're lying to me.

Cell.Text: Hasn't Mercer Frey taught you people anything? | You kill me and your only contact with the East Empire Company vanishes. That's not smart for business.

Node.Caption: TG04GulumEiInitialBranchTopic05a: Give me the buyer's name or I'll kill you. (Intimidate)

Cell.Text: [S] G|I have a buyer looking for a case of Firebrand Wine. There just so happens to be a single case in the cellars of the Blue Palace. | Bring it to me, and we'll talk about Goldenglow Estate.
Good. Can't have the buyer getting impatient and looking elsewhere for this, can we? | Here, take this. I certainly can't use it, but I suppose I need to pay you something for the goods.
[S] Not at all. I consider it an investment in prolonging my life. | As far as Goldenglow Estate goes, I'll tell you what I know.

Node.Caption: TG04GulumEiWineDoneBranchTopic01: You're trying to bribe me now?
